</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-03-02-0059-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-03-02-0059-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>See particularly <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-03-02-0052" class="document">Dinwiddie to GW, 26 April 1756</a>, for references to the ordering out of the militia and to the sending of supplies to Fredericksburg.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-03-02-0059-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-03-02-0059-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>For a recent reference to the Irish beef, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-03-02-0044&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-03-02-0044-fn-0004#GEWN-02-03-02-0044-fn-0004" class="document">GW to Dinwiddie, 24 April 1756, especially note 4</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-03-02-0059-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-03-02-0059-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>See ibid., <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-03-02-0044&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-03-02-0044-fn-0007#GEWN-02-03-02-0044-fn-0007" class="document">note 7</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-03-02-0059-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-02-03-02-0059-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>For references to the minutes of the council of war and the missing letters, see ibid., <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-03-02-0044&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-03-02-0044-fn-0008#GEWN-02-03-02-0044-fn-0008" class="document">note 8</a>.</p>

</div>
